olive oil
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet chicken breast
20 g butter
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ tbs brown sugar
1.5 cup boiling water
1 packet orecchiette
1 cucumber
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
2 radish
¼ packet Pitted Mixed Olives
1 tin Crushed & Sieved Tomatoes
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook diced bacon, breaking up with spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.

• To the chicken, add the butter, crushed & sieved tomatoes, chicken-style stock powder, garlic & herb seasoning, brown sugar and the boiling water (1 1/2 cups for 2 people / 3 cups for 4 people).
• Add orecchiette, stir to combine, then bring to the boil.
• Reduce heat to medium and cover with lid. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pasta is 'al dente', 10-14 minutes.

TIP: Keeping the saucepan covered helps steam to cook pasta!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish. Roughly chop cucumber.
• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, radish, cucumber and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil with salt and pepper. Season.

• Roughly chop pitted mixed olives (see ingredients).
• Remove pasta from heat, then stir through grated Parmesan cheese and olives. Season to taste.
• Divide one-pot chicken and bacon orecchiette between bowls.
• Serve with garden salad. Enjoy!